Visual Recognition¶

Scene Classification Project¶

  1. Image Description based on BoW:

    • Build a vocabulary of visual words by clustering local feature vectors from the training set.
    • Use methods like k-means ([sklearn.cluster.KMeans()]), mean-shift ([sklearn.cluster.MeanShift]), or Gaussian Mixtures ([sklearn.mixture.GaussianMixture]) for clustering.
    • Each cluster centroid represents a visual word.
    • Represent each image with a histogram of visual features occurrences based on the vocabulary.
    • Normalize the histogram to maintain consistency across images.

  2. Classification:

    • Utilize linear classifiers such as support vector machines (SVMs) for multiclass classification.
    • Train N binary 1-vs-all SVMs to classify into N categories.
    • Alternatively, consider using other classifiers like Random Forests.

  3. Assessment:

    • Measure how well BoW works when paired with a classifier:
      1. Accuracy (sklearn)
      2. Confussion Matrix (sklearn)

  1. Extra Credit:

    • Experiment with different parameters and design decisions to enhance performance.
    • Analyze the influence of vocabulary size, feature sampling density, window sizes, etc. (10 points)
    • Explore the effect of PCA on image features. (10 points)
    • Compare results between BoVWs obtained from dense features and keypoints. (20 points)
    • Compare difference between using SVM and another classifier. (10 points)
    • Consider combination of 2 features descriptors. (20 points)
    • Compare hard-assignment and soft-assignment (Fisher Vector) methods. (20 points)

  2. Dataset:

    • https://web.mit.edu/torralba/www/indoor.html
    • Choose 12 categories
    • First 150 images per category, 80 for training, 20 for validation, 50 for testing

def skimage_sift(img, n_hist, n_ori):
    sift = feature.SIFT(n_hist=n_hist, n_ori=n_ori)
    sift.detect_and_extract(img)
    return sift.descriptors

def descriptors(dict_train, dict_test, n_hist, n_ori):
    print('SIFT DESCRIPTORS')

    desc_dict_train = {label: [] for label in set(dict_train.keys())}
    desc_dict_test = {label: [] for label in set(dict_test.keys())}

    for (key_train, values_train), (key_test, values_test) in zip(dict_train.items(), dict_test.items()):

      with Pool(processes = num_cores) as pool:
        des_train = pool.starmap(skimage_sift, [(img, n_hist, n_ori) for img in values_train])
        for des in des_train:
          desc_dict_train[key_train].append(des)

      with Pool(processes = num_cores) as pool:
        des_test = pool.starmap(skimage_sift, [(img, n_hist, n_ori) for img in values_test])
        for des in des_test:
          desc_dict_test[key_test].append(des)

    return desc_dict_train, desc_dict_test


def pca_skimage_sift(img, n_hist, n_ori, n_pca):
    sift = feature.SIFT(n_hist=n_hist, n_ori=n_ori)
    sift.detect_and_extract(img)
    desc = sift.descriptors

    desc = StandardScaler().fit_transform(desc)
    des = sc.pp.pca(desc, n_comps = n_pca,  copy=True, random_state=RANDOM_SEED, svd_solver='arpack')

    return des.astype(np.float32)


def pca_descriptors(dict_train, dict_test, n_hist, n_ori, n_pca):
    print('SIFT DESCRIPTORS - PCA')

    desc_dict_train = {label: [] for label in set(dict_train.keys())}
    desc_dict_test = {label: [] for label in set(dict_test.keys())}

    for (key_train, values_train), (key_test, values_test) in zip(dict_train.items(), dict_test.items()):
        with Pool(processes=num_cores) as pool:
            des_train = pool.starmap(pca_skimage_sift, [(img, n_hist, n_ori, n_pca) for img in values_train])
            for des in des_train:
                desc_dict_train[key_train].append(des)

        with Pool(processes=num_cores) as pool:
            des_test = pool.starmap(pca_skimage_sift, [(img, n_hist, n_ori, n_pca) for img in values_test])
            for des in des_test:
                desc_dict_test[key_test].append(des)

    return desc_dict_train, desc_dict_test

def stack_descriptors(descriptors):
    descriptors = list(chain(*descriptors.values()))
    bag_of_features = np.concatenate(descriptors, axis=0).astype('float32')
    return bag_of_features

def DataSet(descriptors: dict):
    list_images = []
    list_labels = []

    for key_train, values_train in descriptors.items():
      for descriptor in values_train:
        list_images.append(descriptor)
        list_labels.append(key_train)
    return list_images, list_labels

def ExtractFeatures(kmeans, descriptors, image_count, n_clusters):
    im_features = np.zeros((image_count, n_clusters), dtype=np.float32)
    list_images, list_labels = DataSet(descriptors)

    for i in range(image_count):
        features = np.vstack(list_images[i]).astype(np.float32)
        predictions = kmeans.predict(features)
        unique, counts = np.unique(predictions, return_counts=True)
        im_features[i, unique] = counts

    return im_features, list_labels

def ExtractFeatures_FisherVector(gmm, descriptors):
    return fisher_vector(descriptors, gmm)

def BestCluster(descriptors, arrange: tuple = (10, 411, 50)):
    Sum_of_squared_distances = []
    K = np.arange(*arrange)
    print('The range: ', K)
    print('Number of clusters: | ', end="")
    for k in K:
        print(k, '| ', end="")
        km = KMeans(n_clusters = k, n_init='auto', random_state=RANDOM_SEED).fit(descriptors)
        Sum_of_squared_distances.append(km.inertia_)
    print("")
    plt.plot(K, Sum_of_squared_distances, 'bx-')
    plt.xlabel('number of clusters')
    plt.ylabel('Sum of squared distances')
    plt.title('Optimal number of clusters')
    plt.show()

def plotHistogram(img_features, n_clusters, texto):
    x_scalar = np.arange(n_clusters)
    y_scalar = np.array([np.sum(img_features[:,h], dtype=np.int32) for h in range(n_clusters)])
    plt.figure(figsize=(18, 3))
    plt.bar(x_scalar, y_scalar, width=0.5)
    plt.xlabel("Visual Word Index")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.title(f"Complete Vocabulary Generated {texto}")
    plt.xticks(x_scalar + 0.01, x_scalar, fontsize=7, rotation=45)
    plt.show()

Dense Features¶

In [39]:
def ExtractFeaturesDense(img):
  features, labels = pyfeats.gt_features(img, mask = None, deg=4, freq=[0.05, 0.4]) # Gabor Transform (GT)
  gt_dict = dict(zip(labels, features))

  features, labels = pyfeats.glds_features(img, mask = None, Dx=[0,1,1,1], Dy=[1,1,0,-1]) # Basic Gray-Level Distribution Statistics (GLDS)
  glds_dict = dict(zip(labels, features))

  features, labels = pyfeats.fos(img, mask = None) # (First-order statistics (FOS) or Statistical Features (SF))
  sfm_dict = dict(zip(labels, features))

  features, labels = pyfeats.lbp_features(img, mask = None, P=[8,16,24], R=[1,2,3]) # Local Binary Patterns
  lbp_dict = dict(zip(labels, features))

  features, labels = pyfeats.lte_measures(img, mask = None, l=7) # Law's Texture Energy Measures (LTE/TEM)
  lte_dict = dict(zip(labels, features))

  features, labels = pyfeats.zernikes_moments(img, radius=9) # Zernikes Moments
  zernikes_dict = dict(zip(labels, features))

  gt_df = pd.DataFrame(gt_dict, index=[0])
  glds_df = pd.DataFrame(glds_dict, index=[0])
  sfm_df = pd.DataFrame(sfm_dict, index=[0])
  lbp_df = pd.DataFrame(lbp_dict, index=[0])
  lte_df = pd.DataFrame(lte_dict, index=[0])
  zernikes_df = pd.DataFrame(zernikes_dict, index=[0])

  dfs = [gt_df, glds_df, sfm_df, lbp_df, lte_df, zernikes_df]
  texture = pd.concat(dfs, axis=1)
  return texture
